Package projecttwo

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Date
    This class defines a date by year, month, and day from an input String, it also auto-generates a date object with calendar date if no parameter is sent, and checks if dates are valid calendar dates based on the Calendar library
    DateTest
    This class uses JUnit to test the isValid method for the Date class using a variety of different test cases.
    Enrollment
    This class represents the students that are currently enrolled.
    EnrollStudent
    This class represents a student that is enrolled, and must be in the roster.
    International
    This class represents a International student that extends Student and has fields such as profile, major, creditCompleted, and isStudyAbroad.
    InternationalTest
    This class uses JUnit to test the tuitionDue method for the International class using a variety of different test cases.
    NonResident
    This class represents a NonResident that extends Student and has fields such as profile, major, and credit completed.
    Profile
    This class defines a student profile with a lastname, a first name, and a date of birth.
    Resident
    This class represents a Resident that extends Student and has fields profile, major, credit completed, and scholarship.
    Roster
    This class defines a roster consisting of multiple students.
    RosterTest
    This class uses JUnit to test the add method for the Roster class using a variety of different test cases.
    RunProject2
    This class provides a main method for running the enrollment system.
    Student
    This is an abstract class that represents a student.
    TriState
    This class represents a Tristate student that extends NonResident and has fields such as profile, major, creditCompleted, and state.
    TuitionManager
    This class reads input from command line and takes a series of different options such as adding a student, removing a student, changing a major, and printing students in different ways.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Major
    This class defines an enum class for the possible majors.
